.TH "tty_lookup_driver" 9 "tty_lookup_driver" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_lookup_driver \- lookup a tty driver for a given device file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tty_driver *" tty_lookup_driver
.BI "(dev_t device "  ","
.BI "struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "int *index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
device number
.IP "filp" 12
file pointer to tty
.IP "index" 12
index for the device in the \fIreturn\fP driver
.SH "RETURN"
driver for this inode (with increased refcount)

If \fIreturn\fP is not erroneous, the caller is responsible to decrement the
refcount by tty_driver_kref_put.

Locking: tty_mutex protects get_tty_driver
